64 template <typename T, typename U>
65 class CCreateMap {
66 private:
67  std::map<T, U> m_map;
68 public:
69  CCreateMap(const T& key, const U& val) {
70  m_map[key] = val;
71  }
72  CCreateMap<T, U>& operator()(const T& key, const U& val) {
73  m_map[key] = val;
74  return *this;
75  }
76  operator std::map<T, U>() {
77  return m_map;
78  }
79 };

1909 class COptionBase {
1910 private:
1911 public:
1912  COptionBase() {};
1913  virtual ~COptionBase() = 0;
1914  // virtual string SetValue(string) {SU2MPI::PrintAndFinalize("shouldn't be here"); return "";};
1915  virtual string SetValue(vector<string>) = 0;
1916  virtual void SetDefault() = 0;
1917 
1918  string optionCheckMultipleValues(vector<string> & option_value, string type_id, string option_name) {
1919  if (option_value.size() != 1) {
1920  string newString;
1921  newString.append(option_name);
1922  newString.append(": multiple values for type ");
1923  newString.append(type_id);
1924  return newString;
1925  }
1926  return "";
1927  }
1928 
1929  string badValue(vector<string> & option_value, string type_id, string option_name) {
1930  string newString;
1931  newString.append(option_name);
1932  newString.append(": improper option value for type ");
1933  newString.append(type_id);
1934  return newString;
1935  }
1936 };

1941 template <class Tenum>
1942 class COptionEnum : public COptionBase {
1943 
1944  map<string, Tenum> m;
1945  unsigned short & field; // Reference to the feildname
1946  Tenum def; // Default value
1947  string name; // identifier for the option
1948 
1949 public:
1950  COptionEnum(string option_field_name, const map<string, Tenum> m, unsigned short & option_field, Tenum default_value) : field(option_field) {
1951  this->m = m;
1952  this->def = default_value;
1953  this->name = option_field_name;
1954  }
1955 
1956  ~COptionEnum() {};
1957  string SetValue(vector<string> option_value) {
1958  // Check if there is more than one string
1959  string out = optionCheckMultipleValues(option_value, "enum", this->name);
1960  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
1961  return out;
1962  }
1963 
1964  // Check to see if the enum value is in the map
1965  if (this->m.find(option_value[0]) == m.end()) {
1966  string str;
1967  str.append(this->name);
1968  str.append(": invalid option value ");
1969  str.append(option_value[0]);
1970  str.append(". Check current SU2 options in config_template.cfg.");
1971  return str;
1972  }

3660 class COptionPeriodic : public COptionBase {
3661  string name; // identifier for the option
3662  unsigned short & size;
3663  string * & marker_bound;
3664  string * & marker_donor;
3665  su2double ** & rot_center;
3666  su2double ** & rot_angles;
3667  su2double ** & translation;
3668 
3669 public:
3670  COptionPeriodic(const string option_field_name, unsigned short & nMarker_PerBound,
3671  string* & Marker_PerBound, string* & Marker_PerDonor,
3672  su2double** & RotCenter, su2double** & RotAngles, su2double** & Translation) : size(nMarker_PerBound), marker_bound(Marker_PerBound), marker_donor(Marker_PerDonor), rot_center(RotCenter), rot_angles(RotAngles), translation(Translation) {
3673  this->name = option_field_name;
3674  }
3675 
3676  ~COptionPeriodic() {};
3677  string SetValue(vector<string> option_value) {
3678 
3679  const int mod_num = 11;
3680 
3681  unsigned short totalVals = option_value.size();
3682  if ((totalVals == 1) && (option_value[0].compare("NONE") == 0)) {
3683  this->size = 0;
3684  this->marker_bound = NULL;
3685  this->marker_donor = NULL;
3686  this->rot_center = NULL;
3687  this->rot_angles = NULL;
3688  this->translation = NULL;
3689  return "";
3690  }
3691 
3692  if (totalVals % mod_num != 0) {
3693  string newstring;
3694  newstring.append(this->name);
3695  newstring.append(": must have a number of entries divisible by 11");
3696  this->size = 0;
3697  this->marker_bound = NULL;
3698  this->marker_donor = NULL;
3699  this->rot_center = NULL;
3700  this->rot_angles = NULL;
3701  this->translation = NULL;
3702  return newstring;
3703  }
3704 
3705  unsigned short nVals = 2 * (totalVals / mod_num); // To account for periodic and donor
3706  this->size = nVals;
3707  this->marker_bound = new string[nVals];
3708  this->marker_donor = new string[nVals];
3709  this->rot_center = new su2double*[nVals];
3710  this->rot_angles = new su2double*[nVals];
3711  this->translation = new su2double*[nVals];
3712  for (unsigned long i = 0; i < nVals; i++) {
3713  this->rot_center[i] = new su2double[3];
3714  this->rot_angles[i] = new su2double[3];
3715  this->translation[i] = new su2double[3];
3716  }
3717 
3718  su2double deg2rad = PI_NUMBER/180.0;
3719 
3720  for (unsigned long i = 0; i < (nVals/2); i++) {
3721  this->marker_bound[i].assign(option_value[mod_num*i]);
3722  this->marker_donor[i].assign(option_value[mod_num*i+1]);
3723  istringstream ss_1st(option_value[mod_num*i + 2]);
3724  if (!(ss_1st >> this->rot_center[i][0])) {
3725  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3726  }
3727  istringstream ss_2nd(option_value[mod_num*i + 3]);
3728  if (!(ss_2nd >> this->rot_center[i][1])) {
3729  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3730  }
3731  istringstream ss_3rd(option_value[mod_num*i + 4]);
3732  if (!(ss_3rd >> this->rot_center[i][2])) {
3733  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3734  }
3735  istringstream ss_4th(option_value[mod_num*i + 5]);
3736  if (!(ss_4th >> this->rot_angles[i][0])) {
3737  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3738  }
3739  istringstream ss_5th(option_value[mod_num*i + 6]);
3740  if (!(ss_5th >> this->rot_angles[i][1])) {
3741  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3742  }
3743  istringstream ss_6th(option_value[mod_num*i + 7]);
3744  if (!(ss_6th >> this->rot_angles[i][2])) {
3745  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3746  }
3747  istringstream ss_7th(option_value[mod_num*i + 8]);
3748  if (!(ss_7th >> this->translation[i][0])) {
3749  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3750  }
3751  istringstream ss_8th(option_value[mod_num*i + 9]);
3752  if (!(ss_8th >> this->translation[i][1])) {
3753  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3754  }
3755  istringstream ss_9th(option_value[mod_num*i + 10]);
3756  if (!(ss_9th >> this->translation[i][2])) {
3757  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3758  }
3759  this->rot_angles[i][0] *= deg2rad;
3760  this->rot_angles[i][1] *= deg2rad;
3761  this->rot_angles[i][2] *= deg2rad;
3762  }
3763 
3764  for (unsigned long i = (nVals/2); i < nVals; i++) {
3765  this->marker_bound[i].assign(option_value[mod_num*(i-nVals/2)+1]);
3766  this->marker_donor[i].assign(option_value[mod_num*(i-nVals/2)]);
3767  istringstream ss_1st(option_value[mod_num*(i-nVals/2) + 2]);
3768  if (!(ss_1st >> this->rot_center[i][0])) {
3769  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3770  }
3771  istringstream ss_2nd(option_value[mod_num*(i-nVals/2) + 3]);
3772  if (!(ss_2nd >> this->rot_center[i][1])) {
3773  return badValue(option_value, "periodic", this->name);
3774  }

4062  ++counter;

4066  accordingly. ---*/

4068  case EQUILIBRIUM_WALL_MODEL: counter += 3; break;
4069  case NONEQUILIBRIUM_WALL_MODEL: counter += 2; break;
4070  case LOGARITHMIC_WALL_MODEL: counter += 3; break;
4071  default: break;

4075  this wall function type has not been specified correctly. */
4076  if (counter > totalSize) {
4077  string newstring;
4078  newstring.append(this->name);
4079  newstring.append(", marker ");

4081  newstring.append(", wall function type ");

4083  newstring.append(": Additional information is missing.");

4113  this->walltype[i] = it->second;
